==English==
=== Etymology ===
Middle English ''Lady Gunilda'' which was a huge crossbow that used powerful shot. It later became used for firearms like cannons and muskets. The Germanic woman's name "Gundahild" and similar means "war-sword".

===Pronunciation===
*gŭn, /{{IPAchar|ɡʌn}}/, /<tt>gVn</tt>

=== Noun ===
'''gun''' ([[guns]])

#(heavy artillery) a [[bullet]] firing [[weapon]].
#(very portable, short, for hand use) a bullet firing weapon.
#(less portable, long, for hand use) a bullet firing weapon.
#(''slang'') [[penis]].

